
test_ffdh: Test FFDH exchange with parameter generation and
           verification as well as private key generation

Input required for FFDH operation:
- Parameter size or
- Parameters

Output:
- Parameters
- Public key
- Shared key

To run (load and start) container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_ffdh.img

Example for generating parameters of a given size:

1) Send command to generate parameters with given size

$ cmtest cmd -f100 parmgen 1024
CD: Request from HLOS:
CD: 00000000 02 00 00 00 07 00 00 00 70 61 72 6d 67 65 6e 00 |........parmgen.|
CD: 00000010 04 00 00 00 31 30 32 34                         |....1024        |
CD: pbits: 1024
CD: generating for 1024
CD: Params generation succeeded
CI: Closing PKE context
CI: Sending response to HLOS of 4 bytes
CD: Response to HLOS:
CD: 00000000 00 00 00 00                                     |....            |

Example for verifying parameters:

1) Send command to verify parameters followed with the parameters
   you wish to verify

$ cmtest cmd -f100 parmset % % %02
CD: Params verification succeeded
CI: Closing PKE context
CI: Sending response to HLOS of 4 bytes
CD: Response to HLOS:
CD: 00000000 00 00 00 00

Example for doing an exchange:

1) Send command to set parameters followed by the parameters

$ cmtest cmd -f100 parmset % % %02

2) Execute the exchange command

$ cmtest cmd -f100 exchange
CD: Request from HLOS:
CD: 00000000 01 00 00 00 08 00 00 00 65 78 63 68 61 6e 67 65 |........exchange|
CD: Privkey_a generation succeeded
CD: Privkey_b generation succeeded
CD: pubkey_a: 0x103a384
CD: Pubkey_a generation succeeded
CD: Pubkey_b generation succeeded
CD: Sharedkey_a generation succeeded
CD: Sharedkey_b generation succeeded
CI: Closing PKE context
CI: Sending response to HLOS of 4 bytes
CD: Response to HLOS:
CD: 00000000 00 00 00 00                                     |....            |

Example for generating private keys:

1) Send command to set parameters followed by the parameters

$ cmtest cmd -f100 parmset % % %02

2) Execute the private key generation command

$ cmtest cmd -f100 privkey
CD: Request from HLOS:
CD: 00000000 01 00 00 00 07 00 00 00 70 72 69 76 6b 65 79 00 |........privkey.|
CD: Privkey generation succeeded
CI: Closing PKE context
CE: Privkey generation failed.
CI: Sending response to HLOS of 4 bytes
CD: Response to HLOS:
CD: 00000000 84 9f 03 01                                     |....            |

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
